title: I'm Not there (2007)DVDRip
description:
I&#039;m Not There is a Golden Globe Award-winning
 and Academy Award-nominated 2007 biographical 
film inspired by the life of iconic singer-songwriter
 Bob Dylan. It depicts six distinct stages of Dylan&#039;s 
life and public persona portrayed by an ensemble cast
 of actors: Marcus Carl Franklin, Ben Whishaw, Heath 
Ledger, Christian Bale, Richard Gere, and Cate Blanchett,
 who play characters based on Dylan but with different
 names.[1]

The film tells its story using non-traditional
 techniques, similar to the poetic narrative style
 of Dylan&#039;s songwriting. It takes its name from the
 Dylan outtake "I&#039;m Not There", a song never officially
 released until its appearance on the film&#039;s official
 soundtrack album. Critically acclaimed, I&#039;m Not There
 made many top ten film lists for 2007, topping the lists
 for The Village Voice, Entertainment Weekly, Salon and
 The Boston Globe
